The paper discusses a vulnerability in software-defined networking (SDN) that allows an attacker to bypass critical network functions and violate security policies. This vulnerability falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the communication networks aspect of SDN, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper proposes different techniques for exploiting the vulnerability, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses possible countermeasures, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the relevance of the findings beyond the use cases considered in the paper, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
